========
1. Heat oven to 180 C / Gas 4.
2. Break the chocolate into squares and melt it with the butter in a bowl over a saucepan of hot water.
3. Take off the heat and leave to cool.
4. Whisk the egg , egg yolk and sugar with an electric mixer until well mixed.
5. Butter 2 ramekins , about 75mm in diameter.
6. Dust well with the cocoa powder , then shake off any excess.
7. Whisk the cooled chocolate mixture into the eggs and sugar mixture.
8. Sift the flour over the mixture , then fold in.
9. Divide between the 2 ramekins.
10. Bake for 15 minutes in the preheated oven.
11. Run a knife around the edge of each cake and turn out onto plates.
